Dear teacher,<br>
<br>
Your digital exam for the course @{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Vaktitel']} (@{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Vakcode']}) will take place in 3 days.<br>
<br>
<strong>What can I expect during a take-home exam?</strong><br>
Just like with an onsite exam, there will be at least one assistant floor manager (AFM'er) present during the exam to take care of the technical aspect. The AFM'er is present in a live chat at <a href="https://examsupport.uva.nl">https://examsupport.uva.nl</a> for students and in <a href="@{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Teamsmeeting']}">a Teams meeting</a> for you. Shortly before and during the exam, you're expected to be in <a href="@{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Teamsmeeting']}">the Teams meeting</a> together with the AFM'er to answer potential non-technical questions.<br>
The exam is protected with a password (@{substring(items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['W_x002d_nummer'], 1)}) and a timeslot  (@{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Start']} - @{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Einde']}). Students can only start with the exam after entering the password within the aforementioned timeslot. Before the exam starts, you'll have to share the <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/28129/files/7187213?wrap=1">TestVision log in instructions</a>, the password (@{substring(items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['W_x002d_nummer'], 1)}) and the <a href="https://examsupport.uva.nl">https://examsupport.uva.nl</a> link with the students on Canvas.<br>
<br>
<strong>Anything else I still have to do?</strong><br>
